HEADWORD: Retrusion
<hw>Re*tru"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
retruding, or the state of being retruded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In virtue of an endless remotion or <qex>retrusion</qex> of the
constituent cause.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

